    dc:creator "Korsós, Zoltán; Nakamura, Yasuyuki; Tanabe, Tsutomu" ;
    dc:date "2011" ;
    dc:title "Two new millipede species of the genus Riukiaria (Diplopoda, Polydesmida, Xystodesmidae) endemic to the Ryukyu Archipelago, Japan" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277569>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277570> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277569>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2 – 3. Riukiaria maculata sp. n., holotype male. 2 = Live coloration, Tane-ga-shima; 3 = Live specimen in UV-light. FIGURES 4 – 6. Riukiaria mundyi sp. n., paratype specimens. 4 = Live coloration, Yonaguni-jima; 5 – 6 = The same specimens in ambient flashlight, and in UV-light." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277569/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277570>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10 – 13. Riukiaria maculata sp. n. 10 – 12 = Left gonopod of holotype male, lateral, mesal, and apical (ventral) views, respectively; 13 = Left cyphopod of paratype female, posterior view. Scales 0.5 mm. c = coxa, tp = triangular process, v = valve, r = receptacle, op = operculum, other abbreviations as in Fig. 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277570/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

